thread.title: TV | Republic of Telly

author: Fiona Flynn
title: TV | Republic of Telly
text: New series of Republic of Telly kicks off tonight and with a new presenter to boot, as comedienne Joanne McNally joins the show to replace Bernard O'Shea and Jennifer Maguire who have gone off to work on spin-off 'Bridget and Eamon'. Joanne will be joining regular presenter Kevin McGahern with the pair kicking things off in a sketch called TV Licence Inspectors 2. It sees Kevin having to come out of retirement and track down those responsible for TV licence payments grinding to a halt. While Joanne turns to a comedy legend for advice on baking in Silence of the Buns - will she have the same comedy timing as her predecessor Jennifer? We'll just have to wait and see.
